func myFunc(param: Int) -> Int? {if param < 0 {return nil} else if param == 0 {return 1} else {return param * myFunc(param: param - 1)!} }This improved version adds a check for negative input. If the input is negative, it returns nil, indicating an error. Otherwise, it proceeds with the factorial calculation as before.  The use of optional return type and optional chaining prevents the crash.